John Neihart was born in 1802 and in 1829 married Theresa Burger, who was born in 1810. They had seventeen children as follows:
Magdalina, 11-10-1830;
Maria, 10-14-1831;
Barbara, 12-7-1832;
Levi, 4-30-1834;
Elsi or Alice, 6-21-1835;
Jonas, 9-27-1836 (my great-grandfather);
Elizabeth, 8-4-1838;
Simon, 11-25-1840;
Solomon, 3-13-1842;
Amos, 10-28-1843;
Jacob, 3-3-1845;
Phobe, 1-6-1848;
Willhulmus (William), 5-6-1849;
John, 9-1-1850;
James LeRoy, 9-1-1851;
Nicholas (your father), 7-16-1852;
and Adeline, 1-27-1855.

I will now write information about the family of Jonas Neihart. Jonas and Sarah had four children, Obediah, Elsie, Ada, and Harley. Elsie married John Wagstaff and then along with Obediah and his wife moved to Kansas. *Obediah and his wife lived around Carbondale and Osage City, Kansas. They had three daughters, Fern, Addie, and Jessie. Addie and Jessie are still living. *Elsie and John lived near Tecumseh, Kansas. Their children Paul, Beulah, and Letha are still living. Letha has a daughter, Betty (Mrs. Alfred Succi),who we have been to visit at Tecumseh several times during the past ten years. *Ada had one child, Paul Winklepleck. Now we come to *Harley, your first cousin and my grandfather. Harley lived on the farm near Coal City,which has been in the family since 1854. Harley was born in 1875 and died in 1954. He married Nora Brothers in 1893, and they had eleven children as follows:
Carl, born 10-25-1894, died 2-25-1895;
Raymond, born 1-3-1896, died 3-5-1946;
Ralph, born 12-10-1898, died 1-25-1900;
Eva, born 3-16-1901, died 6-8-1964;
Inez, born 9-7-1902 (living);
Gilbert (my father), born 9-10-1904 (living);
Grace, born 4-16-1906 (living);
Sadie, born 2-24-1908, died 4-22-1934;
Fred, born 7-21-1909 (living);
Lola, born 4-23-1911 (living);
Clarence, born 12-9-1912, died 1-19-1972. Starting at the beginning, Raymond has one son. Inez has one daughter, Gilbert has me and a daughter, Lola has two children, and Clarence has three children.
